    <para>The ANF Reference Model is a logical information model describing the format of a
        normalized clinical statement that may have originated from an information system data
        store, a standard-based message (e.g. HL7 Version 2), a standard-document (e.g. HL7 CDA), or a
        standard-based resource (e.g. HL7 FHIR), or an instance of a CIMI model (e.g. FHIR-based profile, openEHR archetype) .</para>
